1
00:00:12,117 --> 00:00:13,827
EDUCATIONAL RIGHTS PROTECTION BUREAU

2
00:00:13,910 --> 00:00:15,912
ALL REPORTS
ARE KEPT CONFIDENTIAL AS A RULE

3
00:00:15,995 --> 00:00:18,790
PLEASE HELP OUR SCHOOL
THIS JUST ISN'T RIGHT

4
00:00:18,873 --> 00:00:20,500
THIS IS DAILY LIFE AT OUR SCHOOL

5
00:00:20,583 --> 00:00:21,835
IT'S REALLY MESSED UP

6
00:00:21,918 --> 00:00:23,044
PLEASE COME HELP, ERPB

7
00:00:26,256 --> 00:00:28,758
I FEEL SO BAD FOR OUR TEACHER

8
00:00:35,098 --> 00:00:37,058
EXPOSING THE STUDENT
WHO ASSAULTED A TEACHER

9
00:00:37,559 --> 00:00:39,435
REPORTING A SERIOUS ASSAULT ON A TEACHER

10
00:00:48,653 --> 00:00:51,072
<i>You will remember</i>
<i>the death of a female teacher</i>

11
00:00:51,156 --> 00:00:53,616
<i>that led to the establishment of the ERPB.</i>

12
00:00:54,117 --> 00:00:57,412
<i>The current Minister of Education</i>
<i>and head of the ERPB, Choi Gang-seok,</i>

13
00:00:58,830 --> 00:01:01,166
<i>is the victim's father.</i>

14
00:01:02,584 --> 00:01:05,211
<i>And Inspector Na Hwa-jin was her fiancé.</i>

15
00:01:08,089 --> 00:01:09,007
<i>Is it truly possible</i>

16
00:01:09,090 --> 00:01:13,261
<i>this has nothing to do with</i>
<i>the teacher killed by her student?</i>

17
00:01:13,970 --> 00:01:16,931
<i>These people are not working</i>
<i>for educational rights.</i>

18
00:01:17,640 --> 00:01:18,975
<i>It is cruel revenge</i>

19
00:01:19,058 --> 00:01:21,603
<i>for the death</i>
<i>of their daughter and fiancée.</i>

20
00:01:22,478 --> 00:01:24,105
<i>It is a personal vendetta.</i>

21
00:01:29,194 --> 00:01:30,111
Im Han-rim.

22
00:01:32,739 --> 00:01:33,698
What are you doing?

23
00:01:34,449 --> 00:01:35,867
Have you eaten, sir?

24
00:01:35,950 --> 00:01:36,784
Yeah.

25
00:01:37,952 --> 00:01:38,870
Let's go.

26
00:01:38,953 --> 00:01:40,705
Did you happen to see

27
00:01:41,706 --> 00:01:42,916
the press conference?

28
00:01:48,463 --> 00:01:49,505
Yeah.

29
00:01:53,509 --> 00:01:55,053
Is it all true?

30
00:01:55,762 --> 00:01:57,096
Yes, it's true.

31
00:02:04,437 --> 00:02:07,148
You'll be late to the meeting
if you just stand there.

32
00:02:07,649 --> 00:02:08,691
Come on, hurry.

33
00:02:13,279 --> 00:02:15,615
We have a lot to do.
Where the hell did everyone go?

34
00:02:20,870 --> 00:02:23,373
They're eccentric and…

35
00:02:24,082 --> 00:02:26,960
The members' eccentric,

36
00:02:27,669 --> 00:02:30,171
ignorant, and tyrannical…

37
00:02:30,880 --> 00:02:34,968
I do not see any potential for improvement

38
00:02:35,468 --> 00:02:37,762
in team members' capabilities--

39
00:02:37,845 --> 00:02:40,306
"Therefore, I am requesting
a transfer of assignment."

40
00:02:40,932 --> 00:02:42,892
Gosh, this is…

41
00:02:42,976 --> 00:02:44,894
ASSIGNMENT TRANSFER APPLICATION

42
00:02:48,273 --> 00:02:49,524
Deputy Bong Geun-dae.

43
00:02:50,316 --> 00:02:51,317
Yes, sir.

44
00:02:51,401 --> 00:02:53,278
What is this font?

45
00:02:54,112 --> 00:02:55,280
It's so eye-catching.

46
00:02:56,447 --> 00:02:57,282
Pardon?

47
00:02:57,365 --> 00:03:00,076
Let's use this font
for all official documents from now on.

48
00:03:05,623 --> 00:03:06,499
Oh, yes.

49
00:03:07,166 --> 00:03:08,668
By the way,

50
00:03:10,253 --> 00:03:11,963
that's not a good enough reason.

51
00:03:12,672 --> 00:03:16,009
If you want to be reassigned,
give me a convincing reason.

52
00:03:16,092 --> 00:03:19,345
A reason I can't logically argue against
in any way.

53
00:03:19,887 --> 00:03:23,141
Otherwise, it comes across as whining
to people like us.

54
00:03:25,852 --> 00:03:26,686
Hello, sir.

55
00:03:26,769 --> 00:03:29,063
We're so damn busy right now.
Get a move on!

56
00:03:29,147 --> 00:03:30,398
Look at the time!

57
00:03:35,737 --> 00:03:36,571
Safe…

58
00:03:45,663 --> 00:03:48,791
This report is about

59
00:03:48,875 --> 00:03:52,378
the assault of a teacher by a male student

60
00:03:52,962 --> 00:03:55,590
at Chukmyeong Foreign Language High.

61
00:03:55,673 --> 00:03:57,467
This is the teacher on the screen.

62
00:03:57,550 --> 00:04:01,804
The informant is a colleague
of the assaulted teacher.

63
00:04:01,888 --> 00:04:05,433
They also sent a video of the incident.

64
00:04:05,516 --> 00:04:07,226
-Play the video.
-Yes, sir.

65
00:04:10,313 --> 00:04:11,230
<i>Park Hyeon-ung!</i>

66
00:04:11,314 --> 00:04:12,940
<i>What the hell are you doing?</i>

67
00:04:13,024 --> 00:04:15,568
All that praise
has gone to your head, hasn't it?

68
00:04:19,614 --> 00:04:20,948
Mr. Cheon, are you okay?

69
00:04:21,032 --> 00:04:23,451
-Are you out of your mind?
-Hey, what's wrong?

70
00:04:23,534 --> 00:04:25,661
-What is it?
-Hyeon-ung, what's gotten into you?

71
00:04:26,162 --> 00:04:27,288
Stop it.

72
00:04:32,543 --> 00:04:35,463
TEACH YOU A LESSON

73
00:04:35,546 --> 00:04:38,424
CHUKMYEONG FOREIGN LANGUAGE HIGH SCHOOL

74
00:04:38,508 --> 00:04:40,593
Wow. Is this a school?

75
00:04:41,094 --> 00:04:43,596
What kind of high school looks like this?

76
00:04:44,305 --> 00:04:45,139
I know, right?

77
00:04:45,765 --> 00:04:49,644
I heard they're the best of their kind.
They're very flashy.

78
00:04:50,520 --> 00:04:53,606
You guys go ahead.
I'll catch up with you shortly, all right?

79
00:04:55,108 --> 00:04:55,983
Let's go.

80
00:04:57,443 --> 00:05:00,113
<i>Grades alone don't guarantee</i>
<i>college entry anymore.</i>

81
00:05:00,196 --> 00:05:01,989
<i>-Especially Seoul National Uni.</i>
<i>-Yes.</i>

82
00:05:02,073 --> 00:05:04,909
<i>When I saw his student records,</i>
<i>he had public speaking…</i>

83
00:05:04,992 --> 00:05:07,328
Chukmyeong Foreign Language High School

84
00:05:07,412 --> 00:05:11,582
actually had a lower profile
than other foreign language high schools.

85
00:05:12,083 --> 00:05:14,752
But after that teacher, Mr. Cheon,
started working here,

86
00:05:15,336 --> 00:05:20,550
more students got into elite colleges,
and this became an elite high school.

87
00:05:20,633 --> 00:05:23,094
<i>-It's because they worked so hard.</i>
<i>-But you weren't…</i>

88
00:05:23,177 --> 00:05:25,012
Is that how he became famous?

89
00:05:25,096 --> 00:05:27,849
It was more because of his character.

90
00:05:28,349 --> 00:05:31,102
He's actually really famous
for being a true educator.

91
00:05:31,686 --> 00:05:32,770
A true educator?

92
00:05:34,480 --> 00:05:35,982
Why would a kid hit him?

93
00:05:36,065 --> 00:05:37,442
<i>You're amazing, seriously.</i>

94
00:05:38,151 --> 00:05:39,277
Gosh, sir.

95
00:05:39,777 --> 00:05:41,988
I'd always hoped to meet you one day.

96
00:05:42,071 --> 00:05:45,783
If I ever had the chance to do so,
I wanted to say thank you.

97
00:05:45,867 --> 00:05:46,701
Right.

98
00:05:48,119 --> 00:05:50,163
Allow me
to formally introduce myself, sir.

99
00:05:50,246 --> 00:05:54,333
My name is Na Hwa-jin.
I'm an inspector from the ERPB.

100
00:05:54,417 --> 00:05:55,293
Right, hello.

101
00:05:55,376 --> 00:05:57,962
I got into the Korea Military Academy

102
00:05:58,045 --> 00:06:00,381
after listening
to your EBS online lectures.

103
00:06:00,465 --> 00:06:03,676
That wouldn't be down to me.
You must have worked very hard for it.

104
00:06:03,759 --> 00:06:07,930
The things you said
now and then during your lectures…

105
00:06:08,014 --> 00:06:09,015
The…

106
00:06:09,891 --> 00:06:11,767
Gosh, this is just…

107
00:06:11,851 --> 00:06:13,102
-Are you all right?
-Wow.

108
00:06:13,644 --> 00:06:16,606
What's happening?
What's wrong with Inspector Na?

109
00:06:16,689 --> 00:06:18,107
What you said was really…

110
00:06:32,121 --> 00:06:33,498
Inspector, can't we just

111
00:06:34,332 --> 00:06:35,458
forget this happened?

112
00:06:36,292 --> 00:06:37,835
We have midterm exams soon.

113
00:06:37,919 --> 00:06:40,421
They're important
to Hyeon-ung and the other students.

114
00:06:40,505 --> 00:06:44,050
But still, he was in the wrong
and should be punished.

115
00:06:50,348 --> 00:06:51,849
Sir,

116
00:06:51,933 --> 00:06:54,727
could I perhaps ask a big favor?

117
00:06:55,895 --> 00:06:56,729
Yes, sure.

118
00:06:56,812 --> 00:06:59,774
You know your sign-off
at the end of your online lectures?

119
00:06:59,857 --> 00:07:02,109
Could you say it just one more time?

120
00:07:02,193 --> 00:07:03,861
"I believe in your potential."

121
00:07:04,445 --> 00:07:06,113
Oh my gosh.

122
00:07:06,781 --> 00:07:11,452
There just so happens to be a blackboard
and chalk right here, so…

123
00:07:11,953 --> 00:07:14,247
May I please ask you to do it?

124
00:07:14,330 --> 00:07:16,290
Gosh, Inspector.

125
00:07:20,670 --> 00:07:22,755
I believe in your potential.

126
00:07:42,316 --> 00:07:43,526
Wow!

127
00:07:44,151 --> 00:07:47,196
-You can't just touch it like that.
-What is all this?

128
00:07:47,280 --> 00:07:49,740
I bought it with my most recent paycheck.

129
00:07:49,824 --> 00:07:52,493
Believe it or not, it's dual monitors.

130
00:07:52,577 --> 00:07:54,495
It has a touchscreen,

131
00:07:54,579 --> 00:07:57,164
and the mounting bracket at the back
comes in handy.

132
00:07:57,665 --> 00:07:59,083
Right, it's a computer.

133
00:08:00,126 --> 00:08:03,462
It's not just any computer.
It's a portable monitor.

134
00:08:03,546 --> 00:08:05,798
The display is 16:9, and it's full HD.

135
00:08:05,881 --> 00:08:09,510
It's 15.6 inches, which is great
for watching Netflix and movies.

136
00:08:09,594 --> 00:08:12,722
And it's optimized for gaming
with the ideal aspect ratio and size.

137
00:08:14,348 --> 00:08:16,017
And see this small thing here?

138
00:08:16,100 --> 00:08:17,268
The white USB-C port.

139
00:08:17,351 --> 00:08:21,897
This single device can supply power
and support display output simultaneously.

140
00:08:23,274 --> 00:08:24,442
So it's expensive.

141
00:08:27,737 --> 00:08:28,571
Nice.

142
00:08:32,908 --> 00:08:36,704
PATIENCE

143
00:08:50,885 --> 00:08:52,887
Are you Park Hyeon-ung?

144
00:08:56,599 --> 00:08:59,644
You assaulted your teacher, Mr. Cheon,
a few days ago.

145
00:08:59,727 --> 00:09:00,895
What was the reason?

146
00:09:03,606 --> 00:09:05,650
If I tell you,
will you let me off the hook?

147
00:09:06,901 --> 00:09:08,152
No, you won't!

148
00:09:08,986 --> 00:09:11,656
Expel me or report me to the police
if you want.

149
00:09:11,739 --> 00:09:13,908
Don't pretend you want to know.

150
00:09:19,580 --> 00:09:21,415
If it's hard to decide,

151
00:09:21,499 --> 00:09:23,918
should I make it easy for you?

152
00:09:30,383 --> 00:09:33,177
Do not make me write
the Chinese character for "patience."

153
00:09:36,013 --> 00:09:40,768
The school still hasn't decided
how to punish that kid, Park Hyeon-ung.

154
00:09:40,851 --> 00:09:44,146
I thought the ERPB could really show them,

155
00:09:44,230 --> 00:09:45,940
so I reported the incident.

156
00:09:46,941 --> 00:09:50,861
Mr. Cheon is like a role model
to many other teachers.

157
00:09:51,987 --> 00:09:55,658
He makes you want to become more like him.

158
00:09:56,742 --> 00:10:01,122
Our school didn't attain elite status
simply because he teaches well.

159
00:10:01,205 --> 00:10:05,167
<i>Mr. Cheon is someone</i>
<i>who stays up all night with the students</i>

160
00:10:05,251 --> 00:10:08,796
<i>and gets more excited than they do</i>
<i>when they are accepted into college.</i>

161
00:10:08,879 --> 00:10:11,424
<i>Once the news spread,</i>
<i>students poured in to enroll.</i>

162
00:10:12,925 --> 00:10:15,010
To hit a teacher like him…

163
00:10:15,094 --> 00:10:18,055
I couldn't just stand by and do nothing.

164
00:10:19,974 --> 00:10:20,975
I see.

165
00:10:33,654 --> 00:10:34,613
Damn it!

166
00:10:39,285 --> 00:10:41,495
When do boys usually hit puberty?

167
00:10:41,579 --> 00:10:43,289
Generally, as hormones change,

168
00:10:43,372 --> 00:10:46,375
it spans from middle school
to the second year of high school.

169
00:10:46,459 --> 00:10:48,210
So he's probably at the end of it.

170
00:10:48,294 --> 00:10:49,920
He's all bravado and rage.

171
00:10:50,004 --> 00:10:53,883
He utterly refuses to listen,
and I bet his grades are utterly bad.

172
00:10:53,966 --> 00:10:56,385
Don't make hasty generalizations…

173
00:10:56,469 --> 00:10:59,305
I mean, I think you're mistaken.

174
00:10:59,972 --> 00:11:00,806
About what?

175
00:11:02,057 --> 00:11:02,892
Park Hyeon-ung.

176
00:11:04,894 --> 00:11:06,562
He's ranked first in his grade.

177
00:11:07,605 --> 00:11:08,647
STUDENT REPORT CARD

178
00:11:10,441 --> 00:11:11,442
He really is.

179
00:11:11,525 --> 00:11:13,027
So why would he…

180
00:11:14,028 --> 00:11:15,321
He's ranked first.

181
00:11:15,821 --> 00:11:17,156
Why would he do it?

182
00:11:25,331 --> 00:11:27,166
EXAM MANAGEMENT OFFICE

183
00:11:29,585 --> 00:11:31,587
ENGLISH DEPARTMENT, TERM 1, 2026
MIDTERM EXAM

184
00:11:40,513 --> 00:11:42,598
VIEWING IS PROHIBITED
TO UNAUTHORIZED PERSONNEL

185
00:11:42,681 --> 00:11:43,516
Oh, hello.

186
00:11:46,352 --> 00:11:47,520
Must be the exam papers.

187
00:11:49,396 --> 00:11:51,982
Yes, I'm the Head of Academic Affairs,

188
00:11:52,066 --> 00:11:53,734
so I have to check them.

189
00:11:55,653 --> 00:11:58,030
Wow, the exam papers are all here.

190
00:11:58,113 --> 00:12:00,658
When I didn't want to study for exams
back in the day,

191
00:12:00,741 --> 00:12:03,702
I used to daydream about stealing
exam papers with my friends.

192
00:12:04,829 --> 00:12:08,165
Coming up with ways to steal exam papers
was more fun than studying.

193
00:12:09,416 --> 00:12:10,626
I was like that too.

194
00:12:11,126 --> 00:12:12,253
Really?

195
00:12:12,753 --> 00:12:14,672
Mr. Cheon, it's an honor.

196
00:12:14,755 --> 00:12:17,132
Right, you can't be in here.
Let's head out.

197
00:12:17,216 --> 00:12:20,261
It's like we've led parallel lives.

198
00:12:21,387 --> 00:12:26,600
So why did Park Hyeon-ung assault you?

199
00:12:28,686 --> 00:12:29,520
I'm not sure.

200
00:12:29,603 --> 00:12:31,230
Do you have any idea at all?

201
00:12:34,233 --> 00:12:37,611
I created a special class not long ago.

202
00:12:37,695 --> 00:12:39,530
Right. A special class?

203
00:12:40,406 --> 00:12:45,077
<i>But I don't think the class</i>
<i>met Hyeon-ung's expectations.</i>

204
00:12:45,578 --> 00:12:49,331
That's right. This is ten
plus two over two plus… What is it?

205
00:12:49,415 --> 00:12:51,000
We learned this in our first year.

206
00:12:51,083 --> 00:12:52,626
We already covered that last time.

207
00:12:52,710 --> 00:12:55,588
The line segment A10 is seven,
and the triangle ABC…

208
00:12:55,671 --> 00:12:57,298
Why are we only doing reviews?

209
00:12:57,381 --> 00:12:59,216
How will this help us in the exam?

210
00:12:59,300 --> 00:13:01,051
We've been doing this for days.

211
00:13:01,886 --> 00:13:03,262
You should study with us.

212
00:13:06,891 --> 00:13:09,518
The class wasn't made just for Hyeon-ung.

213
00:13:10,019 --> 00:13:12,771
I had to take the other students' levels
into account too.

214
00:13:12,855 --> 00:13:16,692
But it was ultimately for his sake,
wasn't it?

215
00:13:17,818 --> 00:13:18,777
I'm not sure.

216
00:13:19,945 --> 00:13:21,614
Isn't that just our perspective?

217
00:13:22,323 --> 00:13:24,033
DETAILED SCHOOL LIFE RECORD

218
00:13:25,242 --> 00:13:26,285
What about it?

219
00:13:26,368 --> 00:13:29,455
I just can't make any sense of it at all.

220
00:13:30,497 --> 00:13:32,541
You're a top student,
so why did you do it?

221
00:13:36,378 --> 00:13:40,257
A student as smart as you
must know what happens

222
00:13:40,341 --> 00:13:42,051
if you assault a teacher.

223
00:13:42,134 --> 00:13:44,929
What on earth made you angry enough
to ignore all this?

224
00:13:48,515 --> 00:13:52,561
These grades could earn you a scholarship
at one of the top three universities.

225
00:13:52,645 --> 00:13:55,940
You studied your butt off for 12 years
to get into college

226
00:13:56,023 --> 00:13:57,691
and even became the top student.

227
00:13:57,775 --> 00:14:00,319
So why are you acting
like you don't care about all that?

228
00:14:01,820 --> 00:14:04,949
I had bad grades, and even I find it odd.
Do your parents know?

229
00:14:15,292 --> 00:14:16,460
<i>To tell you the truth,</i>

230
00:14:16,543 --> 00:14:19,296
<i>I made a mistake</i>
<i>I shouldn't have as a teacher.</i>

231
00:14:19,797 --> 00:14:23,258
Once a year, the parents come to school
for college counseling,

232
00:14:23,342 --> 00:14:25,928
but Hyeon-ung's parents live far away
and couldn't come.

233
00:14:26,011 --> 00:14:27,346
So I paid them a visit.

234
00:14:27,429 --> 00:14:29,264
HYEON-UNG'S KOREAN BUFFET

235
00:14:30,516 --> 00:14:31,850
<i>They ran a restaurant,</i>

236
00:14:32,518 --> 00:14:36,855
<i>but they seemed so busy that I just ate,</i>
<i>pretending to be a customer.</i>

237
00:14:38,816 --> 00:14:39,650
What?

238
00:14:40,234 --> 00:14:41,694
I guess your parents don't know.

239
00:14:44,113 --> 00:14:46,824
Then I'll have to ask them.

240
00:14:48,200 --> 00:14:49,910
Damn it!

241
00:14:53,789 --> 00:14:56,834
Let go! Let go of me!

242
00:14:59,586 --> 00:15:00,587
Do you feel wronged?

243
00:15:01,672 --> 00:15:02,548
Angry?

244
00:15:02,631 --> 00:15:04,174
I said let go of me!

245
00:15:04,675 --> 00:15:05,634
Let go!

246
00:15:05,718 --> 00:15:07,636
Then ask for help.

247
00:15:08,971 --> 00:15:11,890
The first step in getting help
is to ask for it.

248
00:15:17,438 --> 00:15:21,233
Excuse me, Hyeon-ung.
This month's tuition hasn't been paid yet.

249
00:15:22,985 --> 00:15:24,069
<i>Hey, son!</i>

250
00:15:24,153 --> 00:15:26,405
<i>Your </i>hagwon <i>tuition</i>
<i>hasn't been paid yet, has it?</i>

251
00:15:26,488 --> 00:15:29,199
