499
00:31:06,135 --> 00:31:09,639
and had been preparing to enroll here
at Chukmyeong Foreign Language High.

500
00:31:10,139 --> 00:31:13,393
But she never made it
because she missed her final exam.

501
00:31:13,476 --> 00:31:14,477
Is that so?

502
00:31:14,560 --> 00:31:15,687
Yes.

503
00:31:15,770 --> 00:31:19,107
And the student who was able
to come here in her place

504
00:31:19,190 --> 00:31:22,860
was Jung Su-jeong,
the student in your class.

505
00:31:23,361 --> 00:31:24,195
Isn't that right?

506
00:31:27,740 --> 00:31:29,909
Ye-ri had been doing so well in school,

507
00:31:30,451 --> 00:31:32,912
so why did she miss her exam?

508
00:31:32,996 --> 00:31:35,832
Was it because her parents
weren't as privileged as Su-jeong's?

509
00:31:40,003 --> 00:31:44,340
Is that why you created a class
that cut into her study time,

510
00:31:44,424 --> 00:31:46,134
stole her tutor, and pulled strings

511
00:31:46,217 --> 00:31:50,138
to sabotage her parents' store,
pushing her to violence, like Hyeon-ung?

512
00:31:51,055 --> 00:31:53,433
So she would mentally break down
and miss the exam?

513
00:32:03,317 --> 00:32:06,654
What? Do you still have
unfinished business with me?

514
00:32:07,155 --> 00:32:09,407
What do I need to do to end this?

515
00:32:09,907 --> 00:32:10,867
What?

516
00:32:14,537 --> 00:32:16,289
You just need to tell me one thing.

517
00:32:17,290 --> 00:32:18,458
Cheon Sang-yeol.

518
00:32:26,007 --> 00:32:28,551
What Cheon Sang-yeol did to you.

519
00:32:30,386 --> 00:32:31,554
Just tell me that.

520
00:32:43,191 --> 00:32:46,277
You think ranking first in your grade
makes you tier one, don't you?

521
00:32:46,944 --> 00:32:49,989
<i>Each person has a tier</i>
<i>that suits them best.</i>

522
00:32:50,073 --> 00:32:53,493
<i>In your case,</i>
<i>it would be around tier nine.</i>

523
00:32:54,368 --> 00:32:55,995
<i>Your parents are no different.</i>

524
00:32:56,079 --> 00:32:57,872
<i>In fact, your whole family is</i>

525
00:32:58,664 --> 00:32:59,665
tier nine.

526
00:33:04,253 --> 00:33:05,755
Son of a bitch.

527
00:33:06,672 --> 00:33:07,965
Son of a bitch.

528
00:33:20,186 --> 00:33:22,313
She caused a serious problem.

529
00:33:22,396 --> 00:33:24,607
Did you come all the way here
just on her word?

530
00:33:28,778 --> 00:33:33,032
I never said Han Ye-ri
was a problem student.

531
00:33:33,616 --> 00:33:36,285
You barely remembered her a moment ago.

532
00:33:37,203 --> 00:33:40,915
Yet you're well aware of the issues
she caused at Soyeon Girls' High School.

533
00:33:40,998 --> 00:33:43,835
The fact that the ERPB was there
means there was an issue.

534
00:33:44,877 --> 00:33:45,711
But…

535
00:33:48,214 --> 00:33:49,924
what are you playing at here?

536
00:33:50,758 --> 00:33:51,884
I think that's enough.

537
00:33:52,927 --> 00:33:54,428
You know Hyeon-ung…

538
00:33:55,888 --> 00:33:59,267
Park Hyeon-ung,
whom you are so concerned about…

539
00:34:01,978 --> 00:34:04,105
He will definitely take
the upcoming exams.

540
00:34:07,191 --> 00:34:08,568
Will he?

541
00:34:12,822 --> 00:34:13,948
Thank you.

542
00:34:17,994 --> 00:34:18,828
I believe

543
00:34:19,620 --> 00:34:21,372
in the potential of the ERPB.

544
00:34:39,807 --> 00:34:41,809
-Don't you think it's a bit much?
-Yeah.

545
00:34:43,060 --> 00:34:44,187
-It's Hyeon-ung.
-What?

546
00:34:44,270 --> 00:34:45,438
What is he doing here?

547
00:34:46,439 --> 00:34:47,315
What the hell?

548
00:34:50,651 --> 00:34:52,695
How could he even think about showing up?

549
00:34:52,778 --> 00:34:54,113
I know, right?

550
00:34:54,197 --> 00:34:56,365
Wow, so brazen.

551
00:34:56,866 --> 00:34:58,826
If it were me, I'd never come in.

552
00:35:20,932 --> 00:35:22,725
<i>What on earth are you doing?</i>

553
00:35:22,808 --> 00:35:25,478
How come Park Hyeon-ung
is able to take the exams?

554
00:35:25,978 --> 00:35:29,190
For messing up her mock exams,

555
00:35:29,273 --> 00:35:32,360
Su-jeong must now get tier-one marks
in all subjects in the midterms.

556
00:35:32,443 --> 00:35:34,445
I already told you this.

557
00:35:35,238 --> 00:35:36,239
Please have your tea.

558
00:35:36,322 --> 00:35:39,575
If this is how it is, I can't promise you
Superintendent of Education.

559
00:35:40,701 --> 00:35:44,205
Why can't Su-jeong get into tier one
when the others manage to?

560
00:35:44,288 --> 00:35:47,625
I pay you considerably more
than the others do. Is it not enough?

561
00:35:47,708 --> 00:35:49,001
For crying out loud!

562
00:35:49,710 --> 00:35:51,837
It's not my fault
your daughter is a brickhead.

563
00:35:52,421 --> 00:35:53,256
Excuse me?

564
00:35:53,339 --> 00:35:55,591
The others all do it,
so what is it with Su-jeong?

565
00:35:55,675 --> 00:35:58,511
Why set the table
if she can't handle a spoon?

566
00:35:59,262 --> 00:36:00,429
Why are you so brazen?

567
00:36:00,513 --> 00:36:04,100
The Superintendent of Education role?
I can get it without your help.

568
00:36:04,183 --> 00:36:06,727
It's you who has a lot to lose, not me.

569
00:36:06,811 --> 00:36:08,896
Can Su-jeong get into college without me?

570
00:36:10,564 --> 00:36:13,859
So just stay out of it, okay?

571
00:36:13,943 --> 00:36:15,653
I'll handle everything.

572
00:36:16,153 --> 00:36:18,239
And we're in a café. Mind your manners.

573
00:36:32,169 --> 00:36:33,546
Oh, you gave me a fright.

574
00:36:36,007 --> 00:36:37,925
-What are these?
-Hold them up.

575
00:36:38,009 --> 00:36:38,926
What?

576
00:36:42,555 --> 00:36:45,099
Didn't you get over it all
when you ran around the track?

577
00:36:45,182 --> 00:36:46,058
No, I didn't.

578
00:36:49,979 --> 00:36:53,024
It's now past six o'clock,
and I need to add RAM to my computer…

579
00:36:56,152 --> 00:36:58,029
What on earth is the matter with you?

580
00:36:58,112 --> 00:36:59,238
Damn it.

581
00:36:59,322 --> 00:37:01,073
It's Inspector Na Hwa-jin.

582
00:37:01,741 --> 00:37:05,328
-I don't think I recognize him anymore.
-What?

583
00:37:05,411 --> 00:37:08,122
He won't even try
to hear Park Hyeon-ung out!

584
00:37:08,622 --> 00:37:11,542
And he only sides with Mr. Cheon.
For God's sake.

585
00:37:11,625 --> 00:37:13,210
That personal vendetta thing…

586
00:37:13,294 --> 00:37:15,046
It's not like that at all.

587
00:37:17,006 --> 00:37:17,840
Then what is it?

588
00:37:17,923 --> 00:37:19,884
Ever since visiting Han Ye-ri,

589
00:37:19,967 --> 00:37:23,929
Inspector Na Hwa-jin
has been keeping an eye on Mr. Cheon.

590
00:37:24,013 --> 00:37:27,975
He told me to keep looking
into Mr. Cheon's students.

591
00:37:28,059 --> 00:37:32,146
That's why I looked into Noavis Institute
and paid them a visit.

592
00:37:32,646 --> 00:37:33,481
Really?

593
00:37:33,564 --> 00:37:34,607
Yes.

594
00:37:35,316 --> 00:37:37,568
Then why was I the only one
who didn't know?

595
00:37:38,486 --> 00:37:39,445
Why?

596
00:37:39,528 --> 00:37:40,571
Well…

597
00:37:41,322 --> 00:37:44,575
He said you're not very good
at deceiving other people

598
00:37:44,658 --> 00:37:48,120
and that you're a terrible liar.

599
00:37:49,830 --> 00:37:51,165
Damn it.

600
00:37:51,957 --> 00:37:52,792
Gosh.

601
00:37:53,709 --> 00:37:54,710
Whoa.

602
00:38:05,888 --> 00:38:06,722
Deputy Bong.

603
00:38:08,474 --> 00:38:09,809
What's gotten into her?

604
00:38:11,018 --> 00:38:14,855
She says she's acting like this
because she feels guilty.

605
00:38:18,317 --> 00:38:20,694
You call that fast?

606
00:38:38,003 --> 00:38:39,463
Why did you do it?

607
00:38:40,714 --> 00:38:43,467
Why did you pretend
you weren't suspicious of Mr. Cheon?

608
00:38:45,052 --> 00:38:47,096
I didn't pretend.

609
00:38:48,472 --> 00:38:49,849
I hoped otherwise.

610
00:38:52,768 --> 00:38:55,896
I hoped there would be
at least one teacher like that.

611
00:39:00,276 --> 00:39:01,777
I should've known better.

612
00:39:02,486 --> 00:39:04,947
Why didn't you say anything?

613
00:39:05,030 --> 00:39:07,241
I think you could've told me.
Me, of all people.

614
00:39:07,324 --> 00:39:09,535
No, I think you should've told me.

615
00:39:10,035 --> 00:39:12,580
I doubted your intention.

616
00:39:13,080 --> 00:39:15,916
You made me doubt you!

617
00:39:21,839 --> 00:39:22,673
Han-rim.

618
00:39:24,383 --> 00:39:25,217
Yes, sir!

619
00:39:25,801 --> 00:39:27,136
We aren't strangers.

620
00:39:31,015 --> 00:39:32,516
Let's do as we always have.

621
00:39:36,937 --> 00:39:37,771
All right?

622
00:39:39,773 --> 00:39:41,525
Understood, sir!

623
00:39:42,026 --> 00:39:44,820
-That bastard Cheon Sang-yeol did this.
-Damn it.

624
00:39:47,031 --> 00:39:49,992
He's not the type to sit around.
We'll have much more to do.

625
00:39:51,994 --> 00:39:54,371
Where are you going?
I said we'll have more to do.

626
00:39:55,498 --> 00:39:56,332
I was just…

627
00:39:56,415 --> 00:39:57,833
Come here. Just stay here.

628
00:39:57,917 --> 00:39:59,084
Mr. Na Hwa-jin?

629
00:40:04,131 --> 00:40:05,424
We're from the police.

630
00:40:05,508 --> 00:40:08,469
We received reports
that you harmed innocent students

631
00:40:08,552 --> 00:40:11,472
during your time as inspector
at Daehan High and Guun High.

632
00:40:15,768 --> 00:40:19,063
We are enforcing search and seizure
of the ERPB for abuse of power

633
00:40:19,146 --> 00:40:21,023
and violations of recruitment laws.

634
00:40:23,943 --> 00:40:27,363
<i>Following a large-scale search and seizure</i>
<i>of the ERPB,</i>

635
00:40:27,446 --> 00:40:29,657
<i>amid a personal revenge scandal,</i>

636
00:40:29,740 --> 00:40:34,161
<i>the prosecution is investigating</i>
<i>Minister Choi on charges of tax evasion.</i>

637
00:40:34,245 --> 00:40:36,455
<i>They said they would protect</i>
<i>educational rights,</i>

638
00:40:36,539 --> 00:40:39,542
<i>so I had no idea</i>
<i>they would attack our teachers like this.</i>

639
00:40:39,625 --> 00:40:42,044
<i>Especially not someone like Mr. Cheon.</i>

640
00:40:42,127 --> 00:40:45,881
<i>How do you see the ERPB's investigation</i>
<i>into teacher Cheon Sang-yeol?</i>

641
00:40:45,965 --> 00:40:48,509
It feels like the ERPB jumped the gun.

642
00:40:48,592 --> 00:40:50,177
After it was revealed

643
00:40:50,261 --> 00:40:53,222
that the ERPB was borne out
of a personal vendetta

644
00:40:53,305 --> 00:40:56,433
by the victim's father and fiancé
over a two-year-old case,

645
00:40:56,517 --> 00:40:58,394
<i>it seems they tried to muddy the waters</i>

646
00:40:58,477 --> 00:41:01,230
<i>by shifting their targets</i>
<i>from students to teachers.</i>

647
00:41:01,313 --> 00:41:04,900
<i>They likely targeted a well-known figure</i>
<i>like Cheon Sang-yeol</i>

648
00:41:04,984 --> 00:41:06,527
<i>for similar reasons.</i>

649
00:41:08,571 --> 00:41:11,699
It looks like Choi Gang-seok
has screwed up big time.

650
00:41:11,782 --> 00:41:13,367
Should we run some articles?

651
00:41:14,410 --> 00:41:18,330
How about we corner the ERPB
and push to impeach the president?

652
00:41:18,414 --> 00:41:22,459
"We were duped by Minister Choi
when he first proposed the ERPB bill."

653
00:41:24,712 --> 00:41:26,672
Perfect time to shift the blame, isn't it?

654
00:41:36,473 --> 00:41:38,726
Announce we'll hold
a Board of Education meeting.

655
00:41:40,519 --> 00:41:42,062
In the hiring of the inspector,

656
00:41:42,146 --> 00:41:44,898
there was abuse of power
by the Minister of Education.

657
00:41:45,399 --> 00:41:46,817
Do you admit it?

658
00:41:57,870 --> 00:42:00,664
It all played out exactly as you expected.

659
00:42:00,748 --> 00:42:02,625
Impressive connections, don't you think?

660
00:42:02,708 --> 00:42:05,336
The fact that the prosecution,
the police, the press,

661
00:42:05,419 --> 00:42:07,921
and even the tax office
all operated as one is just…

662
00:42:08,005 --> 00:42:10,257
I bet even the president can't match that.

663
00:42:10,341 --> 00:42:12,635
Is this the time to be impressed?

664
00:42:12,718 --> 00:42:14,053
Shouldn't we do something?

665
00:42:14,970 --> 00:42:17,640
We have to stay locked up here
until next week anyway.

666
00:42:17,723 --> 00:42:18,932
Next week? Why?

667
00:42:21,268 --> 00:42:23,771
Chukmyeong High's exams are next week.

668
00:42:24,521 --> 00:42:27,024
They won't let us do anything before then.

669
00:42:27,107 --> 00:42:28,359
Goddamn it.

670
00:42:28,901 --> 00:42:30,903
S sub n equals n squared times a sub n.

671
00:42:30,986 --> 00:42:33,364
Something should come to mind
when you see this.

672
00:42:38,118 --> 00:42:40,371
Right, focus on me.

673
00:42:40,454 --> 00:42:44,541
Okay, here it's n plus one squared
times a sub n plus one…

674
00:42:45,042 --> 00:42:45,959
You're here.

675
00:42:46,043 --> 00:42:47,211
Please take a seat.

676
00:42:53,467 --> 00:42:55,969
I saw you took care of the ERPB
all on your own.

677
00:42:56,053 --> 00:42:57,513
All I have are my connections.

678
00:42:58,430 --> 00:43:01,433
-You were a great help too.
-It was nothing.

679
00:43:02,434 --> 00:43:04,478
Enough about the ERPB.

680
00:43:05,437 --> 00:43:06,563
What about Su-jeong?

681
00:43:09,233 --> 00:43:11,110
Right, ma'am.

682
00:43:24,456 --> 00:43:25,833
What is this?

683
00:43:25,916 --> 00:43:27,835
Tell Su-jeong to memorize it all.

684
00:43:27,918 --> 00:43:30,838
Since she can't handle a spoon,
we should spoon-feed her.

685
00:43:32,506 --> 00:43:34,341
You didn't show the other kids, right?

686
00:43:36,135 --> 00:43:39,471
Please take care of my fundraiser
for the Superintendent of Education.

687
00:43:39,555 --> 00:43:41,014
Don't worry.

688
00:43:41,515 --> 00:43:45,185
We will donate enough
to have your funding overflowing.

689
00:43:45,811 --> 00:43:48,856
If this exam goes well,
you'll be the Superintendent of Education.

690
00:43:49,898 --> 00:43:50,899
My gosh.

691
00:43:54,695 --> 00:43:56,780
When I'm told to provide backup support,

692
00:43:56,864 --> 00:44:02,661
I send necessary materials
to the inspectors and look things up…

693
00:44:02,745 --> 00:44:04,913
You won't get anything
from questioning him.

694
00:44:06,123 --> 00:44:09,293
He's just a public official
who does what his superiors tell him.

695
00:44:11,503 --> 00:44:13,380
Don't waste your energy and let him go.

696
00:44:16,925 --> 00:44:18,969
-Deputy Bong.
-Hey.

697
00:44:19,970 --> 00:44:22,765
They said I'm free to go now.

698
00:44:23,682 --> 00:44:24,975
Bring that thing to me.

699
00:44:27,311 --> 00:44:28,729
Pardon? Bring what…

700
00:44:28,812 --> 00:44:30,814
The assignment transfer application.

701
00:44:31,398 --> 00:44:33,525
I'll sign it off for you,
so bring it to me.

702
00:44:34,109 --> 00:44:34,985
You wanted it.

703
00:44:35,986 --> 00:44:39,948
I thought about it again,
and I've changed my mind a little.

704
00:44:40,032 --> 00:44:41,283
Just bring it, you brat.

705
00:44:41,366 --> 00:44:43,160
But I really thought about it again--

706
00:44:43,243 --> 00:44:44,578
Just bring it to me!

707
00:44:51,168 --> 00:44:52,002
Yes, sir.

708
00:44:53,545 --> 00:44:55,255
-Assignment transfer?
-No, but…

709
00:44:55,339 --> 00:44:56,590
-I really--
-Hurry up!

710
00:44:56,673 --> 00:44:58,550
Yes, sir. I'll go and get it.

711
00:45:00,719 --> 00:45:02,095
I AM REQUESTING A TRANSFER OF…

712
00:45:06,225 --> 00:45:08,185
Please just take a look.

713
00:45:09,019 --> 00:45:09,853
Wait…

714
00:45:18,362 --> 00:45:22,032
The way things are now,
staying at the ERPB won't do you any good.

715
00:45:22,115 --> 00:45:23,575
Inspector Na Hwa-jin,

716
00:45:24,284 --> 00:45:25,369
you sign it too.

717
00:45:28,539 --> 00:45:31,542
I won't think of it as you whining,
so stand tall.

718
00:45:32,960 --> 00:45:34,002
Keep your chin up.

719
00:45:49,601 --> 00:45:50,811
Goodbye.

720
00:46:01,196 --> 00:46:03,115
Oops, sorry.

721
00:46:06,118 --> 00:46:07,703
What? Get back to studying.

722
00:46:08,287 --> 00:46:09,872
Quick, pick it up. It's in the way.

723
00:46:12,249 --> 00:46:13,917
You'll make him cry.

724
00:46:20,716 --> 00:46:22,217
Good morning.

725
00:46:24,052 --> 00:46:26,388
Put your textbooks away,
and shut the other door.

726
00:46:41,153 --> 00:46:42,446
Good luck on the exam.

727
00:47:14,978 --> 00:47:16,063
Take care, sir.

728
00:47:16,146 --> 00:47:18,023
-Goodbye, sir.
-You did well.

729
00:47:18,106 --> 00:47:21,360
<i>What was your real motive</i>
<i>for establishing the ERPB?</i>

730
00:47:22,945 --> 00:47:24,613
Do you seek to avenge your daughter?

731
00:47:25,822 --> 00:47:28,867
Or are you trying
to use your dead daughter

732
00:47:28,951 --> 00:47:30,118
for political gain?

733
00:47:30,953 --> 00:47:33,789
Why did you target the teacher
Cheon Sang-yeol?

734
00:47:33,872 --> 00:47:36,541
As the public turned against you
over revenge allegations,

735
00:47:36,625 --> 00:47:37,751
weren't you deflecting?

736
00:47:42,965 --> 00:47:45,008
EXAM MANAGEMENT OFFICE
RESTRICTED AREA

737
00:47:49,888 --> 00:47:51,807
EXAM MARKING PROGRAM
SELECT TOPIC: CALCULUS

738
00:47:51,890 --> 00:47:53,350
Can you pass that to me?

739
00:47:57,562 --> 00:47:59,398
JUNG SU-JEONG
SUBJECT: CALCULUS

740
00:47:59,481 --> 00:48:00,524
It's correct.

741
00:48:05,404 --> 00:48:06,863
JUNG SU-JEONG, SCORE: 0

742
00:48:09,741 --> 00:48:11,994
Pass me the math exam paper.

743
00:48:13,245 --> 00:48:14,079
Here.

744
00:48:18,000 --> 00:48:19,835
-Pass me the English exam paper.
-Here.

745
00:48:23,505 --> 00:48:25,382
What? What's going on?

746
00:48:35,934 --> 00:48:37,144
Stop the exam immediately.

747
00:48:37,227 --> 00:48:39,187
-What do you mean?
-Stop right now.

748
